result.execSummary:
The defendant David B Low was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine to be paid at a rate of $50.00 per month commencing 9/01/2015 with payment plan fee. Alternate 13 days jail as contempt.

Defendant David B Low in court with attorney Kelsey Morin for Samuel W. Benedict.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count # 2 is dismissed and read in.  
The Court Orders the Following:
FINE: $694.00 
 (To be paid at the rate of $50.00 per month commencing 9/1/2015. Failure to pay, the Court orders 13 days Jail as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).
Plea/sentencing hearing on August 3, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
Authorization to appear received and filed.

Attorney Samuel W. Benedict in court.   Defendant David B Low did not appear.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern, Konrad Paczuski, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Attorney appears by authorization.  Defense requests plea and sentencing date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for August 3, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant David B Low in court with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense requests further proceedings date.  Hearing scheduled for July 1, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant David B Low in court.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant to go to State Public Defender's Office for denial form and return this morning with a completed Petition for Appointment of Counsel.  Court passes matter.  Case recalled at 9:50.  Defendant has been approved for a State Public Defender.  Hearing scheduled for May 22, 2015 at 10:30 am.

Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.   Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.   Defendant is not to operate a motor vehicle unless properly licensed.
Waukesha County Pretrial Screening Services Report by Wisconsin Community Services filed.

Defendant David B Low in court, in custody, with attorney Reisha Alexandra Mitchell.    Attorney appears as friend of the court.  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant is not eligible for State Public Defender representation.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT. 
  Hearing scheduled for April 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.
